</comment>
                            <comment id="14209236" author="ram_krish" created="Thu, 13 Nov 2014 04:15:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CPs are nothing but CoProcessors.  Coprocessors are frameworks that provides some hooks in the master, region server and regions so that the user could control the way some of the operations are performed like flush, compaction, scan, writes etc.&lt;br/&gt;
See RegionObserver, MasterObserver,RegionServerObserver etc.&lt;br/&gt;
The region observers are associated with the regions of a table with which the coprocessors are associated with.  Master observer&apos;s hooks are used whenever operations related to master is happening, similar with RegionServerObservers.&lt;br/&gt;
The main interesting thing is that HBase gives you the opportunity to configure these coprocessors and you could also assign priorities to them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
